        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIG. 3. — Detailed SEM views of: A, the anterior part of the upper jaw showing possible pedicellate teeth of Phlegethontia sp.(MNHN- SOT-II-101076b) from the Stephanian B (Upper Carboniferous) of Montceau-les-Mines, France; B, C, pedicellate teeth of the extant urodele Desmognathus monticola Dunn,1916.Arrows indicate zones of weakness. Abbreviation: p, pedicel. Scale bars: 100 μm." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4665599/files/figure.png" .

